Michael Nadler, CPA, CFP® 
					Founder and President, Co-CIO
					847-940-4040				
Firm founder and President, Michael heads the investment advisory, personal financial planning and wealth management services of the Nadler Financial Group. Mike is a Certified Financial Planner (CFP®), a Certified Public Accountant (CPA), and has obtained the Personal Financial Specialist (PFS) designation from the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants. Prior to founding the Nadler Financial Group he was Director of Financial Services for Waterstone Financial Group, a regional investment firm. He began his career as a tax accountant with Price Waterhouse after graduating with high honors from the University of Illinois-Champaign with a bachelor’s degree in Accountancy. He received his professional education in financial planning from the College for Financial Planning in Denver, Colorado.

 




























