          Jul 15, 2017                         - RelSci Data Update                

          Institutional Holdings Changes      




Background Information:


Nadler Financial Group, Inc. »
Nadler Financial Group specializes in tax efficient investing and the selection and monitoring of mutual fund and institutional investment managers. The firm provides discretionary investment management services through their Focused Investment Objective Program to clients with less than $750,000 in assets under management. The programoffers five allocation objectives: Conservative; Moderately Conservative; Moderate; Growth; and Aggressive Growth. Assets are allocated in one of these five allocation models consistent with the client’s stated investment objectives. Nadler Financial Group monitors performance at the model level and, to the extent necessary; changes or modifications are made at the model level.




